01:14:43,560 --> 01:14:46,350
...and you figured
I'd finally flipped out altogether.

710
01:14:48,150 --> 01:14:52,320
I'm sorry, Emily. Forgive me. L know
what a harrowing day I've caused you.

711
01:14:52,480 --> 01:14:54,400
I suppose you've been sitting here...

712
01:14:54,570 --> 01:14:57,150
...trying to figure out
how to get me to a psychiatrist.

713
01:14:57,320 --> 01:14:58,650
As a matter of fact, I have.

714
01:14:58,820 --> 01:15:01,570
I don't know how you've put up with me
all these years.

715
01:15:04,290 --> 01:15:05,540
I loved you.

716
01:15:09,750 --> 01:15:13,750
My God, Emily, l don't know
how to tell you this. L really don't.

717
01:15:13,920 --> 01:15:16,460
The implications are staggering.

718
01:15:16,630 --> 01:15:19,050
Apparently I entered
a very primitive consciousness.

719
01:15:19,220 --> 01:15:22,140
All I remember is what was
comprehensible to that consciousness.

720
01:15:22,300 --> 01:15:25,430
I don't remember, not clearly,
how l got out of the tank room.

721
01:15:26,850 --> 01:15:28,940
The first thing l remember are the dogs.

722
01:15:29,100 --> 01:15:32,610
I followed a pack of wild dogs to the zoo.
That's how l got there.

723
01:15:34,230 --> 01:15:37,940
In the zoo, l hunted down,
killed, and ate a small sheep.

724
01:15:41,490 --> 01:15:44,120
I was utterly primal.
I consisted of nothing more...

725
01:15:44,280 --> 01:15:47,330
...than the will to survive,
to live through the night...

726
01:15:47,790 --> 01:15:49,120
...to eat...

727
01:15:50,120 --> 01:15:51,460
...to drink...

728
01:15:54,340 --> 01:15:55,500
...to sleep.

729
01:15:59,420 --> 01:16:02,720
It was the most supremely
satisfying time of my life.

730
01:16:06,220 --> 01:16:08,140
I may have killed a man tonight.

731
01:16:09,810 --> 01:16:11,600
I remember...

732
01:16:13,270 --> 01:16:14,980
...beating on a...

733
01:16:23,320 --> 01:16:26,200
You don't know the trouble I had
getting these clothes.

734
01:16:26,370 --> 01:16:29,250
I had to go down to the security office.

735
01:16:30,790 --> 01:16:33,330
They want you to call
the security office right now.

736
01:16:33,500 --> 01:16:36,500
There was some kind of ape loose
in your isolation tank room.

737
01:16:36,670 --> 01:16:40,340
Do you know anything about that?
This ape almost killed a security guard.

738
01:16:40,800 --> 01:16:43,510
You didn't bring some ape
down to that tank room, did you?

739
01:16:48,640 --> 01:16:51,770
Your watch and stuff are
in your jacket pocket. You all right?

740
01:16:52,850 --> 01:16:54,350
Is he all right?

741
01:16:54,520 --> 01:16:56,480
Tell Mason what you've been telling me.

742
01:16:56,650 --> 01:16:59,570
I want to hear Mason's views on all this.

743
01:17:00,490 --> 01:17:03,200
I think Mason's views will be predictable.

744
01:17:05,160 --> 01:17:07,870
My God. There it is...

745
01:17:09,330 --> 01:17:14,080
...a protohuman. The first and original,
truly human form.

746
01:17:14,790 --> 01:17:18,710
Tiny, perhaps four feet high,
completely furred...

747
01:17:18,880 --> 01:17:22,380
...chimp-like, but erect.
No knuckle-walking. Shorter arms.

748
01:17:22,550 --> 01:17:27,220
He's moving along so gracefully.
There's two, three of them.

749
01:17:28,850 --> 01:17:30,260
Bipedal, tiny...

750
01:17:38,730 --> 01:17:43,530
I'm killing- Ý'm killing a goat.

751
01:17:43,700 --> 01:17:45,450
I'm killing...

752
01:17:45,610 --> 01:17:48,320
I'm eating hot flesh.

753
01:17:48,490 --> 01:17:50,910
I'm eating the blood of a goat.

754
01:17:54,080 --> 01:17:55,580
Are you okay?

755
01:17:56,670 --> 01:17:59,130
Beautiful. Beautiful.

756
01:17:59,290 --> 01:18:01,590
It sounded like he was having
a bad trip to me.

757
01:18:01,760 --> 01:18:03,920
Some of these tank trips
can get pretty creepy.

758
01:18:07,010 --> 01:18:08,890
What the hell was that?

759
01:19:03,650 --> 01:19:06,150
Did I wake you? Ýt's Emily.

760
01:19:06,320 --> 01:19:09,200
Eddie, I'm in a kind of wild panic.
I need to talk to you.

761
01:19:22,170 --> 01:19:26,170
I don't know how to put this into words,
but I think that what happened to you...

762
01:19:26,340 --> 01:19:28,470
...was not just
a hallucinatory experience.

763
01:19:28,630 --> 01:19:32,510
I've got this gut feeling that something
phenomenological did actually happen.

764
01:19:32,680 --> 01:19:35,220
That there was some kind
of genetic transformation.

765
01:19:35,390 --> 01:19:38,810
I don't know why I think this,
in defiance of all rationality, but l do.

766
01:19:38,980 --> 01:19:42,310
And now that l do, I'm terrified.
I mean really terrified. Petrified.

767
01:19:42,480 --> 01:19:43,520
So am l.

768
01:19:43,690 --> 01:19:45,730
I don't want you doing
this experiment again.

769
01:19:45,900 --> 01:19:49,110
- L have to find out if it actually happened.
- Put the experiment off.

770
01:19:49,280 --> 01:19:51,200
Until we understand more. Minimize risk.

771
01:19:51,360 --> 01:19:53,950
There's no way you can understand
this before the event.

772
01:19:54,120 --> 01:19:56,040
You may cause
irreversible genetic damage.

773
01:19:56,200 --> 01:20:00,080
I don't think we're dealing with genetics.
We're beyond matter, beyond even energy.

774
01:20:00,250 --> 01:20:02,960
What we're back to is the first thought.

775
01:20:03,380 --> 01:20:06,300
I'm trying to tell you l love you.

776
01:20:06,460 --> 01:20:08,210
I know that.

777
01:20:09,050 --> 01:20:12,840
And I'm trying to tell you,
this is an all-bets-are-off sort of thing.

778
01:20:13,010 --> 01:20:16,310
We may be opening a box that may
scrap our whole picture of space-time.

779
01:20:16,470 --> 01:20:20,730
We might have a link to another universe.
For God's sake, Emily, you're a scientist.

780
01:20:20,890 --> 01:20:22,650
You must know how I feel.

781
01:20:24,650 --> 01:20:27,190
Yes, l know how you feel.

782
01:20:29,490 --> 01:20:32,740
It's very late, Eddie.
Would you like to stay here tonight?

783
01:20:34,990 --> 01:20:38,910
I could do with a little love
and a little reassurance right now.

784
01:20:39,410 --> 01:20:41,330
You'll stay, won't you?

785
01:21:19,200 --> 01:21:22,540
If l come out of that tank anthropoid,
I'll be in a primitive state...

786
01:21:22,710 --> 01:21:26,460
...and impossible to relate to,
so sedate me while I'm still in the tank.

787
01:21:26,630 --> 01:21:29,170
Otherwise you'll have to chase me around
and subdue me.

788
01:21:29,340 --> 01:21:30,920
Okay.

789
01:21:31,090 --> 01:21:34,130
I'll tell you one thing,
you come out looking like an ape...

790
01:21:34,300 --> 01:21:37,390
...and I'm going over to Mass Mental
and commit myself.

791
01:21:37,850 --> 01:21:40,180
If it happens,
we'll bring him down with Amytal.

792
01:21:40,350 --> 01:21:43,730
What do you mean "if it happens"?
Everybody keeps saying "if it happens."

793
01:21:43,890 --> 01:21:46,440
Do you think something is gonna happen?
If you do, I'd like to know.

794
01:21:49,480 --> 01:21:51,940
I'm sorry. I'm just nervous as hell.

795
01:21:52,110 --> 01:21:53,940
Listen, so am l.

796
01:22:57,090 --> 01:22:58,590
Anything happen?

797
01:22:58,760 --> 01:23:01,390
I just checked him 10 minutes ago.

798
01:23:01,890 --> 01:23:03,510
Did you order chicken or turkey?

799
01:23:03,680 --> 01:23:05,430
I hope chicken is all right.

800
01:23:05,600 --> 01:23:08,100
I've got nearly 11.
That's more than two hours now.

801
01:23:08,270 --> 01:23:10,060
I think we should stop this.

802
01:23:10,400 --> 01:23:12,150
I'll tell you frankly, I'm frightened.

803
01:23:12,320 --> 01:23:14,860
We could be screwing around
with his genetic structure.

804
01:23:15,030 --> 01:23:17,110
- How do we stop this?
- Can you bring him down?

805
01:23:17,280 --> 01:23:19,910
- He's gonna be sore.
- We should never have let him do it.

806
01:23:20,070 --> 01:23:24,120
Don't know how we let him talk us into this.
We were humoring him, but he's not crazy.

807
01:23:24,290 --> 01:23:25,910
And we know, deep in our hearts...

808
01:23:26,080 --> 01:23:28,750
...that he may be onto something
beyond our comprehension.

809
01:23:28,920 --> 01:23:31,210
Now, because l believe him,
I want this thing stopped.

810
01:23:36,340 --> 01:23:37,420
Oh, Jesus.

811
01:24:14,790 --> 01:24:20,800
Eddie!

812
01:24:20,970 --> 01:24:22,970
No!

813
01:24:23,550 --> 01:24:26,310
Eddie! No, no!

814
01:24:31,730 --> 01:24:35,270
No, no! Eddie!

815
01:26:44,240 --> 01:26:45,360
Oh!

816
01:26:48,820 --> 01:26:49,950
Ah!

817
01:27:41,670 --> 01:27:51,470
Eddie!

818
01:31:19,550 --> 01:31:20,590
His signs are all good.

819
01:31:20,760 --> 01:31:23,260
He'll probably sleep a day or two,
come out stuporous.

820
01:31:23,430 --> 01:31:25,060
He's got a load of drugs in him.

821
01:31:25,220 --> 01:31:28,440
It's not uncommon for a psychedelic
experience to whack you out.

822
01:31:28,600 --> 01:31:31,060
You'd hardly call this
just a psychedelic experience.

823
01:31:31,230 --> 01:31:33,230
His heart is good. His pressure is good.

824
01:31:33,400 --> 01:31:35,110
I'm more worried about you
than l am about him.

825
01:31:35,280 --> 01:31:36,860
I'm all right.

826
01:31:45,160 --> 01:31:48,250
Of all the men in this world,
why do l have to love this one?

827
01:31:48,410 --> 01:31:50,170
I can't get him out of me.

828
01:31:50,330 --> 01:31:53,250
Do you know how many men
I tried to fall in love with this year?

829
01:31:53,420 --> 01:31:56,250
No matter who I'm in bed with,
I have to imagine it's him.

830
01:31:56,420 --> 01:31:58,630
No matter who I'm eating with
or walking with...

831
01:31:58,800 --> 01:32:01,180
...there's always this pain
because it isn't him.

832
01:32:02,140 --> 01:32:04,390
I'm possessed by him.

833
01:32:07,350 --> 01:32:09,390
Oh, it's crazy.

834
01:32:10,390 --> 01:32:12,690
I think that's the way it's supposed to be.

835
01:32:12,860 --> 01:32:15,520
- He doesn't give a damn about me.
- You're the only thing he cares about...

836
01:32:15,690 --> 01:32:17,650
...outside of his work.
- No, Mason.

837
01:32:18,780 --> 01:32:22,320
I was never real to him. Nothing in
the human condition was ever real to him.

838
01:32:22,490 --> 01:32:23,910
He's a truth lover.

839
01:32:24,080 --> 01:32:28,790
Reality to Eddie is only that
which is changeless, immutably constant.

840
01:32:28,960 --> 01:32:32,960
What happened to Eddie tonight,
that was Eddie's idea of love.

841
01:32:34,130 --> 01:32:36,630
That was consummation. Ha, ha.

842
01:32:36,800 --> 01:32:39,380
He finally got it off with God.

843
01:32:39,550 --> 01:32:43,680
He finally embraced the absolute,
was finally ravished by truth...

844
01:32:43,840 --> 01:32:46,890
...and it goddamn near destroyed him.

845
01:32:48,140 --> 01:32:50,390
He never loved me.
You knew him as well as l did.

846
01:32:50,560 --> 01:32:54,730
We were all bits
of transitory matter to him.

847
01:32:56,360 --> 01:33:00,650
All right, now, you're going into shock.
I'm going to get you something.

848
01:33:14,420 --> 01:33:17,670
We reached a point tonight
where physical science just breaks down.

849
01:33:17,840 --> 01:33:19,300
We're in blue skies.

850
01:33:19,460 --> 01:33:22,010
Tonight was history,
and what are we gonna do about it?

851
01:33:22,170 --> 01:33:26,180
I'm gonna do nothing about it.
Tonight scared the hell out of me.

852
01:33:26,350 --> 01:33:28,260
That tank just blew up.

853
01:33:28,430 --> 01:33:31,680
Whatever happened inside that tank
released a hell of a lot of energy.

854
01:33:32,770 --> 01:33:36,520
For God's sake, let's drop this goddamn
thing. I don't want to talk about it.

855
01:33:36,690 --> 01:33:39,400
I can't help it.
You may want to go to sleep right now...

856
01:33:39,570 --> 01:33:42,490
...but the way I feel
I don't expect to go to sleep for a year.

857
01:33:42,650 --> 01:33:44,610
I'm on fucking fire.

858
01:33:44,780 --> 01:33:49,030
I am in there mopping up the goddamned
tank room and l would like to know why.

859
01:33:49,200 --> 01:33:51,370
Do you believe in
supernatural agencies, Mason?

860
01:33:51,540 --> 01:33:53,000
No, sir, l do not.

861
01:33:53,620 --> 01:33:56,790
Then what we saw tonight
was a physical phenomenon.

862
01:33:56,960 --> 01:34:00,210
An inexplicable physical phenomenon.
If it's phenomenological...

863
01:34:00,380 --> 01:34:03,970
...then it's explicable. I've got to know why.
Let me talk, for chrissake.

864
01:34:04,130 --> 01:34:07,050
I have been in there mopping up
that tank room for three hours.

865
01:34:07,220 --> 01:34:08,890
I've had all I can take.

866
01:34:09,060 --> 01:34:11,180
I can tell you
what I would like to do.

867
01:34:11,350 --> 01:34:13,480
We have got to repeat this
with other subjects.

868
01:34:13,640 --> 01:34:15,140
We need a selective sample.

869
01:34:15,310 --> 01:34:18,060
We will put up a notice
in the student union for volunteers.

870
01:34:18,230 --> 01:34:20,900
- Get five or six subjects.
- This is Arthur talking, right?

871
01:34:21,070 --> 01:34:23,610
Step up the doses of the drug.
- Conscience of science?

872
01:34:23,780 --> 01:34:27,240
Check them against Eddie's values.
- Petitions against genetic engineering.

873
01:34:27,410 --> 01:34:29,950
We could even get a grant, for chrissake!

874
01:34:30,120 --> 01:34:32,790
Big, moral science of the people...
- Bullshit!

875
01:34:32,950 --> 01:34:36,750
...and here you are, willing to use an
untested drug on innocent human beings.

876
01:34:36,920 --> 01:34:39,250
Please stop shouting.

877
01:34:48,090 --> 01:34:49,430
How are you?

878
01:34:50,430 --> 01:34:52,600
Would you like to go back to sleep?

879
01:34:54,310 --> 01:34:55,600
Yes.

880
01:34:56,730 --> 01:34:59,230
Would you mind if Mason
had a quick look at you first?

881
01:35:01,690 --> 01:35:03,440
It's a good idea.

882
01:35:06,320 --> 01:35:08,740
Maybe you ought to have
a quick look at him, Mason.

883
01:36:12,050 --> 01:36:13,970
Oh, l hope it isn't the kids.

884
01:36:15,260 --> 01:36:16,680
Hello?

885
01:36:20,020 --> 01:36:22,850
Everything's fine, Arthur. He's fine.

886
01:36:23,020 --> 01:36:25,520
- Lt's Arthur. Are you fine?
- Yes.

887
01:36:26,820 --> 01:36:30,400
Arthur, I'll call you back
when I'm more awake. Everything's fine.

888
01:36:35,120 --> 01:36:37,540
God, I wonder what time it is.

889
01:36:37,910 --> 01:36:39,910
I should call the kids.

890
01:36:41,830 --> 01:36:43,830
I can't tell you
how much you mean to me...

891
01:36:44,670 --> 01:36:48,210
...how much l need you and the kids.
I just wanted you to know that.

892
01:36:48,380 --> 01:36:51,970
You saved me. You redeemed me
from the pit. L was in it, Emily.

893
01:36:52,130 --> 01:36:56,970
I was in that ultimate moment of terror
that is the beginning of life.

894
01:36:57,140 --> 01:36:59,060
It is nothing.

895
01:36:59,930 --> 01:37:02,520
Simple, hideous nothing.

896
01:37:03,730 --> 01:37:07,570
The final truth of all things
is that there is no final truth.

897
01:37:08,900 --> 01:37:12,360
Truth is what's transitory.
It's human life that is real.

898
01:37:12,530 --> 01:37:16,530
I don't want to frighten you, but I'm trying
to tell you is at that moment of terror...

899
01:37:16,700 --> 01:37:20,540
...is a real and living horror,
living and growing within me now.

900
01:37:21,040 --> 01:37:24,290
And the only thing that keeps it
from devouring me is you.

901
01:37:24,460 --> 01:37:26,580
Why don't you just come back to us?

902
01:37:27,920 --> 01:37:30,420
Hmm. It's too late.

903
01:37:30,590 --> 01:37:33,470
I don't think l can get out of it anymore.

904
01:37:33,760 --> 01:37:36,720
I can't live with it. The pain is too great.

905
01:37:45,020 --> 01:37:48,820
Defy it, Eddie.
You made it real. You can make it unreal.

906
01:37:48,980 --> 01:37:50,570
If you love me, Eddie...

907
01:37:50,730 --> 01:37:53,780
If you love me- Eddie, defy it!

908
01:37:58,410 --> 01:37:59,660
Argh!

909
01:38:14,800 --> 01:38:15,840
Ugh!

910
01:39:40,260 --> 01:39:41,680
I love you, Emily.

